reviewText: love it for was well protected
I bought this because it follows the story of one of my favorite Jing adventures. It Didn't let me down!

i was already a jing fan so i'm a little biased, still  as much as i loved seeing some of his past, (he's such a cute little kidly wink) it wasn't as good as the series, but still a realy worthwhile show to see.

Since I am a big fan of the original Jing, I had to own this one as well. If you have seen the first and liked it, this is a must have. It tells of Jings beginnings and how he teamed up with Kir. It is, however, nothing like the original series. Good, but not what I expected.
